during WWII - was S/S Politician. Having left Liverpool two days earlier,

in bad weather, containing 250,000 bottles of whisky. The locals gathered 
as many bottles as they could, before the proper authorities arrived, and 
even today, bottles are found in the sand or in the sea every other year.
